headline: Boeing Stock Falls Below This Crucial Level As FAA Grounds MD-11 Jets
summary: On Saturday, the FAA issued an order to ground all MD-11 planes while the crash is investigated. An MD-11 operated by United Parcel Service crashed last Wednesday.

headline: United States Short Haul Road Freight Transport Industry Report 2025: Market to Reach $202 Billion by 2033 from $147.83 Billion in 2024 with FedEx, UPS, and DHL at the Forefront
summary: The United States Short Haul Road Freight Transport Market is projected to grow from US$ 147.83 billion in 2024 to US$ 202 billion by 2033, with a CAGR of 3.53% from 2025-2033. Key drivers include e-commerce expansion, just-in-time inventory, and technological advancements. Challenges include rising fuel costs and urban restrictions. headline: Local Business Owner Celebrates New Venture with Opening of a New PostalAnnex in Tucson, Arizona
summary: Annex Brands, Inc., one of the leading franchisors in the packing, shipping, and office services industries, is excited to announce the opening of its newest PostalAnnex location in Tucson, AZ, to owners, Josh and Lani Baker. This new PostalAnnex brings new life to the location, which was formerly a Ship n' Mail Xpress that was operating for over 25 years.
